By Awayi Kuje  Akwanga â€“ Nacabs Polytechnic,Akwanga,Nasarawa State, says it has awarded free tuition scholarship to over 150 students studying in the institution. Mr David Abuluya, the Founder of the institution, disclosed this to News Agency of Nigeria(NAN) in Akwanga on Sunday. Abuluya said that the aim of the gesture was to encourage less
privileged children who wanted to go to school but could not afford the
fees. According to him, those given scholarship would enjoy free tuition for the period of their studies in the institution. He advised the students against cultism activities,examination
malpractice and other vices, warning that the institution would deal
with any of them who indulged in such acts..